S1603.topicName: Characteristics of People by Language Spoken at Home

S1603.universe: Although the American Community Survey (ACS) produces population, demographic and housing unit estimates, for 2010, the 2010 Census provides the official counts of the population and housing units for the nation, states, counties, cities and towns. For 2006 to 2009, the Population Estimates Program provides intercensal estimates of the population for the nation, states, and counties.

S1601.universe: Although the American Community Survey (ACS) produces population, demographic and housing unit estimates, for 2010, the 2010 Census provides the official counts of the population and housing units for the nation, states, counties, cities and towns. For 2006 to 2009, the Population Estimates Program provides intercensal estimates of the population for the nation, states, and counties.

DP03.universe: NOTE. Although the American Community Survey (ACS) producespopulation, demographic and housing unit estimates, it is theCensus Bureau's Population Estimates Program that produces anddisseminates the official estimatesof the population for the nation, states, counties, cities andtowns and estimates of housing units for states and counties. For more information on confidentiality protection, samplingerror, nonsampling error, and definitions, see SurveyMethodology.

DP04.universe: NOTE. Although the American Community Survey (ACS) producespopulation, demographic and housing unit estimates, it is theCensus Bureau's Population Estimates Program that produces anddisseminates the official estimatesof the population for the nation, states, counties, cities andtowns and estimates of housing units for states and counties. For more information on confidentiality protection, samplingerror, nonsampling error, and definitions, see SurveyMethodology.

For 2006 to 2009, the Population Estimates Program provides intercensal estimates of the population for the nation, states, and counties.

S1401.universe: Although the American Community Survey (ACS) produces population, demographic and housing unit estimates, for 2010, the 2010 Census provides the official counts of the population and housing units for the nation, states, counties, cities and towns. For 2006 to 2009, the Population Estimates Program provides intercensal estimates of the population for the nation, states, and counties.

S2502.topicName: DEMOGRAPHIC CHARACTERISTICS FOR OCCUPIED HOUSING UNITS

S2502.universe: Although the American Community Survey (ACS) produces population, demographic and housing unit estimates, it is the Census Bureau's Population Estimates Program that produces and disseminates the official estimates of the population for the nation, states, counties, cities and towns and estimates of housing units for states and counties.

S2502.topicName: DEMOGRAPHIC CHARACTERISTICS FOR OCCUPIED HOUSING UNITS

S2502.universe: Although the American Community Survey (ACS) produces population, demographic and housing unit estimates, it is the Census Bureau's Population Estimates Program that produces and disseminates the official estimates of the population for the nation, states, counties, cities and towns and estimates of housing units for states and counties.

S2502.topicName: DEMOGRAPHIC CHARACTERISTICS FOR OCCUPIED HOUSING UNITS

S2502.universe: Although the American Community Survey (ACS) produces population, demographic and housing unit estimates, it is the Census Bureau's Population Estimates Program that produces and disseminates the official estimates of the population for the nation, states, counties, cities and towns and estimates of housing units for states and counties.

S1501.universe: Although the American Community Survey (ACS) produces population, demographic and housing unit estimates, for 2010, the 2010 Census provides the official counts of the population and housing units for the nation, states, counties, cities and towns. For 2006 to 2009, the Population Estimates Program provides intercensal estimates of the population for the nation, states, and counties.

S2301.universe: Although the American Community Survey (ACS) produces population, demographic and housing unit estimates, for 2010, the 2010 Census provides the official counts of the population and housing units for the nation, states, counties, cities and towns. S2301.universe: Although the American Community Survey (ACS) produces population, demographic and housing unit estimates, it is the Census Bureau's Population Estimates Program that produces and disseminates the official estimates of the population for the nation, states, counties, cities and towns and estimates of housing units for states and counties.
